      • setMaximumNumberOfVertices

        public void setMaximumNumberOfVertices(long maxN)
        Sets the maximum number of vertices that will be loaded from a source file. Useful in memory constrained environments
        Parameters:
        maxN - the maximum number of vertices.

      • setPreSortEnabed

        public void setPreSortEnabed(boolean enabled)
        Set the loader to pre-sort the vertices to improve their spatial locality before processing. Default is to not sort vertices.
        Parameters:
        enabled - true if the sort is enabled; otherwise, false.

      • readInputFile

        public List<org.tinfour.common.Vertex> readInputFile(TestOptions options)
                                              throws IOException
        Read the LAS file as specified in the supplied options, applying any settings such as maxNumberOfVertices or setPreSortEnabled that are passed as part of the options object.
        Parameters:
        options - a valid options object
        Returns:
        a list of vertices (potentially empty)
        Throws:
        IOException - in the event of a non-recoverable I/O condition such as file-not-found.
